<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>Comparison · 2026</div>
    <h1 class="hero-h">Claude Team vs <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">Claude Enterprise.</em></h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">Claude Team works for most companies under 200 employees. Claude Enterprise becomes necessary when SSO, audit logs, or compliance requirements would otherwise block adoption. Here's the decision framework — and why most companies that "feel like" they need Enterprise actually don't.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">The framing</span>
    <h2 class="h2">What each tool is actually built for</h2>
    <p class="body">Claude Team is $30/seat/month (annual billing, 5-seat minimum). It includes shared Projects, central billing, admin controls, and standard usage limits — enough for most B2B teams under 200 employees.</p>
    <p class="body">Claude Enterprise is custom-priced (typically $60–$100+/seat/month with annual commits). It adds the things larger orgs require to deploy at scale: SSO/SCIM, audit logs, expanded context windows (up to 500K tokens), dedicated account management, and stronger data residency controls.</p>
    <p class="body">The wrong reason to choose Enterprise: "we're a real company, we should have the enterprise plan." The right reason: a specific feature that's blocking your adoption.</p>
    
    <div class="vs-grid">
      <div class="vs-card"><h3>Claude</h3><ul><li>Shared Projects across the team</li><li>Central billing and admin controls</li><li>5x higher usage limits than Pro</li><li>Admin role management</li><li>Standard support</li><li>Works for most companies under 200 employees</li></ul></div>
      <div class="vs-card"><h3>Claude Enterprise</h3><ul><li>SSO + SCIM for user provisioning</li><li>Audit logs for compliance</li><li>Up to 500K token context window</li><li>Stronger data residency controls</li><li>Dedicated account management</li><li>Custom Terms of Service and DPAs</li></ul></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">Side-by-side</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Feature comparison</h2>
    <table class="compare-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Capability</th><th>Claude</th><th>Claude Enterprise</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody><tr><td>Shared Projects</td><td>★★★★★</td><td>★★★★★</td></tr><tr><td>Central billing</td><td>★★★★★</td><td>★★★★★</td></tr><tr><td>Admin controls</td><td>★★★ (basic roles)</td><td>★★★★★ (granular)</td></tr><tr><td>SSO / SCIM</td><td>—</td><td>★★★★★</td></tr><tr><td>Audit logs</td><td>—</td><td>★★★★★</td></tr><tr><td>Context window</td><td>Standard (200K)</td><td>Extended (up to 500K)</td></tr><tr><td>Data residency controls</td><td>Standard</td><td>Custom</td></tr><tr><td>Support level</td><td>Standard</td><td>Dedicated account team</td></tr><tr><td>Pricing</td><td>$30/seat/mo (annual)</td><td>$60–$100+/seat (custom)</td></tr><tr><td>Minimum commitment</td><td>5 seats</td><td>Negotiated annual</td></tr></tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">Use cases</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Which one for which job</h2>
    <h3 class="h3">Claude Team is the right answer when:</h3><p class="body">— Your team is under ~200 people<br/>— You don't have hard SSO/SCIM requirements yet<br/>— You're early in your AI deployment and don't know exactly what you'll need<br/>— You want to keep procurement simple and ship fast<br/>— Cost-per-seat matters more than enterprise feature parity</p><h3 class="h3">Claude Enterprise is the right answer when:</h3><p class="body">— Your security team has formally required SSO/SCIM for new SaaS<br/>— You're in a regulated industry (healthcare, finance, legal) and need audit logs<br/>— You're processing documents longer than ~150K words (extended context)<br/>— You have 200+ users to deploy and Team plan's admin features can't handle the scale<br/>— You need a custom DPA or specific data residency</p><h3 class="h3">Stay on Pro (skip Team) when:</h3><p class="body">— You're 1–4 people and don't need shared Projects yet<br/>— You're still in early experimentation phase</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">FAQ</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Common questions</h2>
    <div class="faq"><h3>How much does Claude Enterprise actually cost?</h3><p>Anthropic doesn't publish Enterprise pricing. Realistic floors based on what we see in actual contracts: $60–$100/seat/month for typical mid-market deals, higher for very small deployments (under 25 seats), lower for very large ones (1000+ seats) with annual commitments.</p></div><div class="faq"><h3>Can I upgrade from Team to Enterprise mid-contract?</h3><p>Yes — Anthropic supports migration from Team to Enterprise. Most companies do this 6–12 months after starting on Team, when they've outgrown the Team plan's features.</p></div><div class="faq"><h3>Do I need Enterprise for HIPAA or compliance work?</h3><p>For HIPAA specifically, Enterprise is required (Team doesn't support BAAs). For SOC2 alone, Team is usually fine since Anthropic itself is SOC2-compliant. Check with your security team.</p></div><div class="faq"><h3>What about the extended context window?</h3><p>Claude's standard context is 200K tokens — roughly 150K words. Enterprise can extend to 500K tokens. This matters if you're routinely working with documents longer than ~150K words (long legal contracts, codebases, multi-document research). For most business workflows, the standard context is sufficient.</p></div><div class="faq"><h3>Should I get Enterprise just for the dedicated support?</h3><p>Probably not, unless you're deploying to 100+ users. For smaller deployments, standard support is responsive and most issues get resolved quickly.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">Related</span>
